list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: + All units now have a unique portrait

task.summary: Default task
Units are now properly removed from battle after they are killed
OutOfManaException now will be thrown before you are asked to choose a target instead of after
Took to updating area of effect, now will properly work. Must fill in stubs for inherited methods in the NPC class to make area of effect work correctly for NPC's as well

Refactored the CharacterUnit hierarchy so area of effect attacks work for both NPC's and PlayableCharacterUnit's targeting allies and enemies. Introduced a max health system so units cannot be overhealed.
CharacterUnits now will only be affected by statusEffects for a set amount of turns
Fixed a bug where area of effect attacks were trying to target more enemies then there were
Added two new classes, Bard and Lancer concurrentmodificationexception will no longer be thrown when removing status effects
Added an item system to the game that allows allies to use items on themselves to restore mana and health.
Created isSelfBuff method in the Ability class in order to allow abilities beside Defend to target oneself automatically.
Created the TacticBaseBattle, Board, and BoardSpace classes to start creating a gui.
Started toward making the graphical user interface starting with the main menu and select Characters screen
CharacterSelect now is correctly proportioned
+ Added Thief class + Added Character Portraits for each of the 4 playableCharacters + statChart is now more dynamic
+ Bar graph now displays values on a more comparative level + Tweaked some stats for the Bard and Lancer class
+ Created basic interface for a battle
+ Characters can now move when it is their turns + Started to work towards creating a selectable menu for units to select their abilities
+ Characters now have 2 action token which they can use on abilities of moving during a turn + NPC's now have a basic network of actions when it comes to their turn
+ Fixed a bug that would not have the Highest and Lowest value be correct in the statsheet class
+ Playable characters can now target units
+ Area of Effect and Items will now work as intended
+ Status Effects now properlly stack when both a debuff and buff are applied to the same Character. + Added new Scenario and LandType
+ Added a character stat menu that is accesible during a Battle + Each status effect is now it's own Class
+ Updated how the status effect classes work + Improved character status screen in battle
+ Have new original character. + Added the StatBonus class that gives each unique character bonus stats + Added unique abilities for each unit
+ Seperated StatusEffects into decaying vs permanent and introduced invulnerablity.
+ StatusEffects effects now take place in their respective constructors instead of in the SupportiveAbility Class
+ Fixed a bug with items and rooted targets having the wrong target. + Improved the functionality of how abilities are sequenced
+ Added the rescue personal ability for Graham + Each character now has a unique CharacterSprite
+ Changed how targeting baord space and units work to now probe nearby spaces instead of the whole board
+ Attacking before taking a movement no longer soft locks the game
+ Updated Status Effects system + Updated Item Effects and they now correctly target + Updated Job abilities to be stand alone
+ updated CharacterSelect to now correctly centre the regions on them
+ implemented a more clean and navigatable battle menu
+ Added experience points and a level up function
+ updated main menu to look for fleshed out
+ updated CharacterSelect graphics to be more dynamic
+ Added the TargetType class and sub classes to remove how abilities target outside of the ability itself
+ Updated startOfTurnPopup to be more visable and clear + Added new HealthBar class for Combat
+ Added HealthBar class
+ Added SurroundingTarget and MovementTarget to their own class instead of being inner classes
+ Unavailable options in the menu are now greyed out + StatusEffectList now contains permanent StatusEffect's
+ Added a status effect indicator that is visable on top of a unit during comabe
+ When selecting a target for an ability, spaces now light up at your cursor hovers them
+ Updated setHandlers in the TargetType class and subclasses to work in phases of confirmation, displaying more information and being more clear
+ Added a damage preview for when units are targeting
- Solved Memory problems when multiple units are being attacked at once
+ Added miss as a popup option during combat + Updated Victory and Defeat Screen + User can now save the scenarios they have completed
+ Updated Enemy Ai to now correctly work
+ All units now have a unique portrait
